bib.title: Deformation in 28Si produced via the 16O+12C reaction

free_txt: Compiled by Gopal Mukherjee
Experimental data were compared with the
theoretical predictions of the statistical model code,
CASCADE
alpha particles were detected using a
Si(SB) detector telescope (DE ~ 10um and E ~ 5mm).
The typical solid angle covered by the telescope was
~ 0.3 msr. The calibration of the telescope was
done using elastically scattered 16O ion from a Au
target, as well as a 229Th-alpha source. Inclusive
energy distributions for the LCPs were measured in the
laboratory angular range of 11deg - 29deg, which
covered the angular range about 25deg - 70deg in the
center-of-mass frame.
No information on source of the uncertainty
Self-supporting 12C target of thickness ~514
micro-gm/cm2
